  "short_text": "Identify the Mistake - Sum of First N Natural Numb",
  "content": "Write a program to recursively compute the sum of the numbers from 1 to N.<hr><b>Input</b><br/><br/>The input will be a single line containing a positive integer (N).<hr><b>Output</b><br/><br/>The output should be a single line containing the sum of the first N natural numbers.<hr><b>Explanation</b><br/><br/>For example, if the given N is 4, your code should print the sum of numbers from 1 to 4. So the output should be 10.",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "HTML",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "70f92bf5-4924-405c-ab25-82892f4b94f3",
      "code_content": "def sum_of_numbers(n):\n    if n == 1:  # Base case\n        return 1\n    else:\n        return n + sum_of_numbers(n-1)  # Recursion\n\n\nnum = int(input())\nresult = sum_of_numbers(num)\nprint(result)\n",
